flowchart LR
    A([Dev Complete]) --> B[Peer Code Review]
    B --> C{Tests Pass?}
    C --> |Fail| A
    C --> |Pass| D[QA Validation]
    D --> E{QA Sign-off?}
    E --> |No| A
    E --> |Yes| F[Security Scan]
    F --> G{Clear?}
    G --> |No| H[Fix Vulnerabilities]
    H --> F
    G --> |Yes| I[VP Engineering Approval]
    I --> J([Production Release])

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION – Post-release monitoring and rollback path
    J --> K[15-Min Automated Monitoring]
    K --> L{Error Rate &<br>Latency OK?}
    L --> |Breach| M[Automatic Rollback]
    M --> N[Page On-Call Engineer]
    N --> A
    L --> |Healthy| O([Release Marked Stable])

    classDef monitoring fill:#e0f0ff,stroke:#2980b9,stroke-width:2px
    classDef rollback fill:#fde8e8,stroke:#c0392b,stroke-width:2px
    classDef stable fill:#e8fde8,stroke:#27ae60,stroke-width:2px

    class K,L monitoring
    class M,N rollback
    class O stable

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Extended the diagram past "Production Release" with a 15-minute automated monitoring window that checks error rate and latency. Added an exclusive gateway: if thresholds are breached, the flow triggers an automatic rollback followed by paging the on-call engineer (who then feeds back to Dev Complete for a fix). If metrics stay healthy, the release is marked stable and the process closes out. Applied distinct style classes for monitoring, rollback, and stable-release nodes for visual clarity.